[[div class="notation"]]
[[=]]
++* MISCOMMUNICATIONS NOTICE
[[/=]]

//"A semiohazard, informally, is a fact of the universe that just shouldn't be true, but functionally is. They are inherently abstract and affect the way that we think and communicate about reality."//

[[>]]
[[size 90%]]//-- Intro to Semiospherics//[[/size]]
[[size 90%]]//S. M. Katz, Esq. et al//[[/size]]
[[/>]]

-----

A particularly costly example of a semiohazard: 'the operations of 'YWTGTSYT' are [*/scp-4703 perfectly legal],' one which has obligated the Foundation Legal Department to entirely redraft Texas' corporate laws.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**NOTE:** Bureaucratohazards are a subset of semiohazard affecting bureaucratic systems.[[/span]] These things are perceived facts of baseline reality; they always have been, and always will be, apparently true. But they //shouldn't//, and we //know// they shouldn't. They aren't part of reality because reality says so, but because reality has been pulled inside-out by the perceptual nature of semantic equivalence.

Read on, knowing that you must accept what the universe says is true, even if it doesn't make sense; one plus one doesn't always equal two.

[[>]]
[[size 90%]]//-- Dr. Eli Forkley//[[/size]]
[[size 90%]]//Director of [*/domc-hub Miscommunications]//[[/size]]
[[/>]]
[[/div]]

