[[include component:image-block
|name=https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/calibri-s-mega-cool-art-page-it-s-mostly-just-icons-but-what/Volatility
|caption=A symbolic identifier representing 'VOLATILITY', apparently abstracted from SCP-INTEGER's original Risk Class.
|align=right
|width=275px]]

**##green|SECURITY MEASURES##:** ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## must only be semantically identified using 'correct' identifiers, including '##blue|NAME##', '##blue|BEING##', '##blue|ENTITY##' and others. However, '##blue|SCP-INTEGER##' is the suggested identifier, due to others being either redundant or only conditionally 'correct'.

Knowledge of ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## and its properties should be restricted to only the necessary personnel for containment, including Dr. Placeholder and one member of the Department of Miscommunications, enforceable via amnesticization. However, extensions for research purposes may be permitted by Dir. Forkley on a case-by-case basis. Note that this ##green|FILE## has been strictly organized such that non-abstract information concerning ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## and/or ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## instances is not directly communicated via identifiers. For the sake of clarity, correct identifiers for ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## and ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## have been made distinct via blue and green coloration (respectively). Updates to this ##green|FILE##, if any, are encouraged to remain consistent with these principles.

##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## instances that do not possess sapience are to be contained at Site-15. Access to such instances for research of semiontological anomalies (a.k.a. semiohazards) may be permitted to personnel possessing Level 4 clearance or higher. With regards to ##green|SCIENTIST## instances, ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## instances possessing sapience need not be contained unless, as a result of their properties or otherwise, they inhibit the containment of ##blue|SCP-INTEGER##.

----

**##green|EXPLANATION##:** ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## is a ##blue|HAZARD##[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]A semiontological anomaly (semiohazard) is a disruption of the Semiosphere (the medium through which information about reality travels before it is perceived or measured) which results in reality's apparent adherence to some non-real axiom.[[/span]] ##blue|COMPLEX## that simplifies 'incorrect' designations and classifications of itself and instances of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT##. In the event that ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## is 'incorrectly' designated or classified through any form of semantic communication, said identifier becomes abstracted[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Abstraction: The generalization of a concept.[[/span]] by one Cuil.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]The Cuil is a unit of measurement denoting one level of abstraction away from the reality of a situation.[[/span]] The new, abstracted identifier is retroactively incorporated into the ##blue|CONSTRUCT## as 'correct'. Additionally, its respective medium of communication will become an instance of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT##.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**##red|LESSON##**[[/span]]

The consequences of ##blue|SCP-INTEGER##'s effects are as follows:

* ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## is, has always been, and will always be identified using names that it has retroactively caused to be factually correct, and the use of any other identifier is considered incorrect. This is also true of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## instances.
* Incorrect identification of the ##blue|SCP-INTEGER##, from baseline perspective, has never occurred, due to retroactive creation of objective fact. However, the state of this ##green|FILE## indicates that it has been published with incorrect designations multiple times, and subsequently became an instance of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT##.

Due to its tendency to make useful labels and categorizations redundant, ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## poses significant nomenclative difficulties to Site-15 documentation and personnel. Due to its semantic nature, ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## shares similarities with memetic hazards, and a single incorrect designation could lead to the rapid propagation of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## throughout Site-15 and its documents, crashing file systems and potentially causing several other containment breaches by preventing effective communication.

Other known 'correct' identifiers for ##blue|SCP-INTEGER## include:

* '##blue|THING##'
* '##blue|CONSTRUCT##' (when referring to semantics)
* '##blue|CHALLENGE##' (when referring to containment)
* '##blue|INFLUENCE##' (when referring to potential disruption)
* '##blue|VOLATILITY##' (when referring to immediate risk)
* '##blue|HAZARD##', '##blue|HAZARD COMPLEX##' (when referring to semiontological phenomena)
* [##green|RESTRICTED## //PER PROTOCOL [*/taboo 4000-ESHU]//][[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**##red|FORBIDDEN##**[[/span]] (when referring to narrative and/or pataphysical elements)
* '##blue|ISSUE##' (when referring to difficulty)[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]See **##green|ADDITION INTEGER-LETTER##**[[/span]]

##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## is the designation for ##green|THINGS##, including both ##green|ITEMS## and ##green|BEINGS##, that have served as a medium of communication for an incorrect designation or classification of ##blue|SCP-INTEGER##. Upon becoming an instance of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT##, its identifiers are similarly abstracted by ##blue|SCP-INTEGER##. Incorrect identifications of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT## instances will be abstracted, but their respective media of communication do not become further instances.

The following is a list of known instances of ##green|SCP-INTEGER-DIGIT##.

